HEADWORD: Lake
<hw>Lake</hw> <pr>(l⟦amac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>laque</ets>, fr. Per. See <er>Lac</er>.]</ety> <def>A pigment
formed by combining some coloring matter, usually by precipitation, with
a metallic oxide or earth, esp. with aluminium hydrate; <as>as, madder
<ex>lake</ex>; Florentine <ex>lake</ex>; yellow <ex>lake</ex>,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lake</ent>⟦br⟧

